HEADWORD: Towardliness
<hw>To"ward*li*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being towardly; docility; tractableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The beauty and <qex>towardliness</qex> of these children moved her
brethren to envy.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Towardly</ent>⟦br⟧
